**Blocs:**
Left (SDAPÖ + KPÖ): [+ aus_left_bloc +]% · [+ aus_left_seats +] seats
Center-Right (CS + GDVP + LB): [+ aus_center_bloc +]% · [+ aus_cr_seats +] seats
Fascist (Heimatblock[? if dnsap_formed : + DNSAP ?]): [+ aus_fascist_bloc +]%

Now — which government takes office?

- @popular_front_austria: Popular Front — SDAPÖ governs with KPÖ support
- @center_right_austria: Center-Right — CS leads with GDVP and LB
- @right_coalition_austria: Right Coalition — Heimatblock forces its way in
- @stalemate_austria: No stable majority — political deadlock

@popular_front_austria
view-if: aus_left_seats >= 83 and kpo_seats < (sdapo_seats * 0.5)
on-arrival: {!
    Q.relation_austria  = (Q.relation_austria  || 0) + 4;
    Q.austria_govt      = 0;
    Q.aus_in_popular_front = 1;
    Q.kpd_relation      = (Q.kpd_relation      || 0) + 6;
    Q.left_strength     = (Q.left_strength     || 30) + 4;
    Q.pro_republic      = (Q.pro_republic      || 50) + 3;
    Q.years_in_government = 0;
    Q.aus_coalition_name = "Popular Front";
!}

= Popular Front — Vienna Stands

The SDAPÖ takes the chancellery. The KPÖ extends parliamentary support from outside cabinet — not a formal coalition, but a working majority for the democratic left.

Red Vienna's municipal socialism now has a national stage.

[? if nsdap_r >= 20 or dnvp_r >= 15 : The Austrian Popular Front sends a powerful signal across the border to those resisting fascism in Germany. ?]
[? if kpo_relevant : The Communists are strong enough that SDAPÖ will need to make real concessions — this government will lean further left than some in the party are comfortable with. ?]

**Government:** SDAPÖ Chancellor · KPÖ parliamentary support · [+ aus_left_seats +] seats

- @root: Continue.

@center_right_austria
view-if: aus_cr_seats >= 83 and cs_vote >= 22
on-arrival: {!
    Q.relation_austria  = (Q.relation_austria  || 0) - 1;
    Q.austria_govt      = 1;
    Q.aus_in_center_right = 1;
    Q.years_in_government = 0;
    Q.aus_coalition_name = "Center-Right";
    // LB in coalition gives it swing leverage
    Q.lb_leverage = Q.lb_seats >= 8 ? 1 : 0;
!}

= Center-Right — The Bourgeois Bloc

The Christian Socials lead a center-right coalition with the Greater Germans and the Landbund. A stable, conservative government — but one that depends on agrarian and nationalist partners who pull in different directions.

[? if lb_swing : The Landbund holds real leverage — rural Austria will demand its price. ?]
[? if heimwehr_kingmaker : The Heimatblock watches from the opposition benches, ready to make trouble. ?]
[? if dnsap_formed and dnsap_threat : The DNSAP lurks as a permanent destabilising force — the Right Coalition will be under pressure to appease them. ?]

**Government:** CS Chancellor · GDVP + LB support · [+ aus_cr_seats +] seats

- @root: Continue.

@right_coalition_austria
view-if: (aus_right_seats >= 83) and (heimatblock_vote >= 10 or dnsap_vote >= 10)
on-arrival: {!
    Q.relation_austria  = (Q.relation_austria  || 0) - 4;
    Q.austria_govt      = -1;
    Q.aus_in_right_coalition = 1;
    Q.pro_republic      = (Q.pro_republic      || 50) - 6;
    Q.years_in_government = 0;
    Q.aus_coalition_name = "Right Coalition";
    Q.austria_authoritarian_drift = (Q.austria_authoritarian_drift || 0) + 1;
    if (Q.dnsap_vote >= 15) Q.austria_authoritarian_drift++;
!}

= Right Coalition — The Fascist Veto

The Heimatblock has forced its way into government. The Christian Socials and nationals accept paramilitary support to build a majority — and in doing so, hand the Heimwehr a key to the door.

The facade of Austrian parliamentary democracy begins to crack.

[? if dnsap_major_threat : **The DNSAP's strength makes even the Heimatblock nervous.** Two competing fascist movements now jostle inside and outside the coalition. ?]
[? if heimatblock_vote >= 20 : With this result, talk of dissolving parliament outright is no longer theoretical. ?]

**Government:** CS or Heimatblock Chancellor · Right Coalition · [+ aus_right_seats +] seats

- @root: Continue.

@stalemate_austria
view-if: aus_left_seats < 83 and aus_cr_seats < 83 and aus_right_seats < 83
on-arrival: {!
    Q.austria_govt = Q.austria_govt || 0;
    Q.aus_in_stalemate = 1;
    Q.austria_crisis = 1;
    Q.pro_republic = (Q.pro_republic || 50) - 3;
    Q.gov_stability = (Q.gov_stability || 50) - 10;
!}

= Deadlock — No Majority Formed

No bloc commands 83 seats. The chamber is paralysed.

A caretaker government continues in office. Fresh elections may follow — or something worse.

[? if dnsap_major_threat : **With the Nazis this strong, new elections would likely make things worse, not better.** ?]
[? if austria_crisis : The Republic may not survive another round of voting in this climate. ?]

- @root: Continue.
